<subSubSection id="62DD65401949296A74C2FB2CFEDCF98C" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1949296A74C2FB2CFF3EFAE3" blockId="25.[144,1104,1261,1643]" box="[144,252,1261,1284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">
<heading id="713081A71949296A74C2FB2CFF3EFAE3" box="[144,252,1261,1284]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" reason="5">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A74C2FB2CFF3EFAE3" box="[144,252,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A7836CB1949296A74C2FAD5FEDCF98C" blockId="25.[144,1104,1261,1643]" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">
The female differs from that of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A7648FAD4FD79FACB" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1926" box="[538,699,1300,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A7648FAD4FD79FACB" box="[538,699,1300,1324]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the evenly strongly impressed longitudinal rugulosities along entire surface of the basal area of metapostnotum (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1949296A74CAFA95FECEFA8B" box="[152,268,1364,1388]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[212,279,1398,1420]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1366]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[212,1172,168,1366]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Females of Megalopta. (A) Lateral view of head of M. guimaraesi Santos &amp; Silveira from Alto Paraíso de Goiás, Brazil; (B‒F). posterolateral view of mesosoma; (B) M. nitidicollis Friese from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. aeneicollis Friese from Novo Airão, Brazil; (D) M. aegis Vachal from Caldas Novas, Brazil; (E) M. chaperi Vachal from Amajari, Brazil; (F) M. amoena Spinola from Alenquer, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004463/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A7537FA94FE05FA8B" authorityName="Vachal" authorityYear="1904" box="[357,455,1365,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A7537FA94FE05FA8B" box="[357,455,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. aegis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A7656FA94FD6AFA8B" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1926" box="[516,680,1364,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulciventris">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A7656FA94FD6AFA8B" box="[516,680,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. sulciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the basal area of metapostnotum often orangish, entirely finely rugulose, stronger rugulosities rectilinear and long along entire surface (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1949296A752DFA52FE31FA4C" box="[383,499,1427,1451]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[212,279,1398,1420]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1366]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[212,1172,168,1366]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Females of Megalopta. (A) Lateral view of head of M. guimaraesi Santos &amp; Silveira from Alto Paraíso de Goiás, Brazil; (B‒F). posterolateral view of mesosoma; (B) M. nitidicollis Friese from Rio Branco, Brazil; (C) M. aeneicollis Friese from Novo Airão, Brazil; (D) M. aegis Vachal from Caldas Novas, Brazil; (E) M. chaperi Vachal from Amajari, Brazil; (F) M. amoena Spinola from Alenquer, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004463/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
). The male is distinguished from that of 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A7795FA54FF76FA2C" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulciventris">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A7795FA54FF76FA2C" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. sulciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the F6–F11 basally with glabrous area levelled to remainder of flagellomere surface, metanotum with very dense pilosity covering entire disc, obscuring the integument in dorsal view, and by basal area of metapostnotum light orangish brown (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1949296A74BAF9D2FE9FF9CC" box="[232,349,1555,1579]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[212,279,1401,1423]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[212,1172,168,1369]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Males of Megalopta. (A, B) Lateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. aeneicollis Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (B) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (C‒F) posterolateral view of mesosoma; (C) M. sulciventris Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (D) M. aeneicollis Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (E) M. aegis Vachal from Caldas Nova, Brazil; (F) M. nitidicollis Friese from São Paulo de Olivença, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004471/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A75E6F9D5FDD6F9CC" authorityName="Vachal" authorityYear="1904" box="[436,532,1556,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegis">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A75E6F9D5FDD6F9CC" box="[436,532,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. aegis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDC74D481949296A761DF9D5FD30F9CC" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1926" box="[591,754,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulciventris">
<emphasis id="18B3EAD91949296A761DF9D5FD30F9CC" box="[591,754,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">M. sulciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the basal area of metapostnotum entirely finely rugulose, and with its posterior margin slightly raised (
<figureCitation id="B2FC2A4E1949296A74CAF992FECCF98C" box="[152,270,1619,1643]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[212,279,1401,1423]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1369]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[212,1172,168,1369]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Males of Megalopta. (A, B) Lateral view of mesosoma; (A) M. aeneicollis Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (B) M. yanomami sp. n. from Parauapebas, Brazil; (C‒F) posterolateral view of mesosoma; (C) M. sulciventris Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (D) M. aeneicollis Friese from Manaus, Brazil; (E) M. aegis Vachal from Caldas Nova, Brazil; (F) M. nitidicollis Friese from São Paulo de Olivença, Brazil. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4004471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4004471/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="600">Figure 6D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
